NAME
     Silly::Krad - Make text hard to read...

SYNOPSIS
       use Silly::Krad;

       # Create a new K-Rad encoder/decoder

       my $Krad=Silly::Krad::new();

       # Encode some text to KRad

       my $Text="Convert me to K-Rad\n";
       my $Encoded=$Krad->encode($Text);

       # Decode KRad text

       my $Decoded=$Krad->decode($Encoded);

       print "$Encoded\n$Decoded\n";

DESCRIPTION
     Silly::Krad (K-Rad) is useful for encoding text documents to make
     them harder to read.  Impress your friends, 31337 hax0rs and
     others.

     Silly::Krad switches letters and numbers with other characters that look
     similar.  For example, "hello world" becomes "h311o wor1d".

AUTHOR
